title: F/i - Milwaukee - Sep 1989 - Hawkwind Heads take heed :)   --FLA
description:
Much kudos to zombiewoof on Dime who seeded this on 18th March, especially for his inclusion of &#039;HAWK HEADS LOOK!&#039; in the Dime page title. Yep, a good move.

sample at:

Quality: 7

Imagine Lou Reed / Velvet Underground (circa White Light White Heat) crossed with Space Ritual-era Hawkwind. And vocals are replaced by plenty of spacey synth bits. That&#039;s pretty much what F/i sound like.

"From Milwaukee, Wisconsin, has been around since 1981, releasing half a dozen LPs on RRRecords. The band started out as a unit elaborating on noise structures in the tradition of Throbbing Gristles "Heathen Earth" or Nurse With Wound&#039;s "Insect" and "Individual Silenced". F/i throbs like a stub toe. The band sounds like "Space Ritual"-era Hawkwind, Roxy Music circa "For Your Pleasure", and Spaceman 3 at their best. Applied to this retro-art-psychedelic thing is the fine sonic landscaping of late &#039;70s-early &#039;80s industrial music."
-Johan Kugelberg - New Revolutions - Details Magazine

Track six (threshold) has been given a post-Dime tidy-up, as there were several volume dropouts near the end.

Richard Frenecki - guitar/processing/treatments
Brian Wensing - guitar/space box
Tom Schnear - bass
Jan Schober - drums
Grant Richter - electronics
